benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/admin/cache - Invalidates the given Cache if specified, otherwise invalidates all caches

covered: Deleting all caches without cacheName returns 204 (TC01, TC08).
Deleting a specific cache by name returns 204 (TC02).
Handling for existing cache but not alive returns 400 (TC04).
Validation for empty cacheName parameter returns 400 (TC05).
Validation for very large cacheName length returns 400 (TC10).
Validation for special characters in cacheName returns 400 (TC11).
Case sensitive behavior for mixed-case cacheName is tested (TC12).
Regression test for problematic cacheName format returns 400 (TC15).
No caches configured or all caches empty results in 204 (TC08).
Performance considerations for large numbers of caches (TC13).
Concurrent requests to invalidate all caches are tested (TC14).
Query parameter handling with extra parameters and with invalid values (TC09).
gaps: Caching headers validation and overall caching behavior (ETag, Cache-Control) not tested.
Rate limiting/throttling scenarios for rapid successive DELETE requests not tested.
Soft delete semantics for caches (if applicable) not tested.
recommendations: Add tests to validate caching headers and caching behavior in DELETE responses (ETag, Cache-Control).
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests to ensure stability under bursts of DELETE requests.
Clarify and test soft delete semantics if caches support a soft-delete pattern, and ensure consistent error codes across similar invalid inputs.
